09/11/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- European Parliament (EP) President Josep Borell pledged continued support for Bulgaria's entry into the EU in 2007, during a meeting with Bulgarian Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg in Brussels late last week. According to a government press statement released Monday (8 November), Borell gave assurances that the next EP report on Bulgaria would acknowledge the progress achieved in the EU accession process and the country's stabilising role in the Balkans. (Monitor - 09/11/04; Bulgarian government Web site, BNR - 08/11/04)
